3697static void set_remap_table_entry(struct amd_iommu *iommu, u16 devid,
3698 struct irq_remap_table *table)
3699{
3700 irq_lookup_table[devid] = table;
3701 set_dte_irq_entry(devid, table);
3702 iommu_flush_dte(iommu, devid);
3703}
3704
3705static struct irq_remap_table *alloc_irq_table(u16 devid)
3706{
3707 struct irq_remap_table *table = NULL;
3708 struct irq_remap_table *new_table = NULL;
3709 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
3710 unsigned long flags;
3711 u16 alias;
3712
3713 spin_lock_irqsave(&iommu_table_lock, flags);
3714
3715 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
3716 if (!iommu)
3717 goto out_unlock;
3718
3719 table = irq_lookup_table[devid];
3720 if (table)
3721 goto out_unlock;
3722
3723 alias = amd_iommu_alias_table[devid];
3724 table = irq_lookup_table[alias];
3725 if (table) {
3726 set_remap_table_entry(iommu, devid, table);
3727 goto out_wait;
3728 }
3729 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&iommu_table_lock, flags);
3730
3731 /* Nothing there yet, allocate new irq remapping table */
3732 new_table = __alloc_irq_table();
3733 if (!new_table)
3734 return NULL;
3735
3736 spin_lock_irqsave(&iommu_table_lock, flags);
3737
3738 table = irq_lookup_table[devid];
3739 if (table)
3740 goto out_unlock;
3741
3742 table = irq_lookup_table[alias];
3743 if (table) {
3744 set_remap_table_entry(iommu, devid, table);
3745 goto out_wait;
3746 }
3747
3748 table = new_table;
3749 new_table = NULL;
3750
3751 set_remap_table_entry(iommu, devid, table);
3752 if (devid != alias)
3753 set_remap_table_entry(iommu, alias, table);
3754
3755out_wait:
3756 iommu_completion_wait(iommu);
3757
3758out_unlock:
3759 spin_unlock_irqrestore(&iommu_table_lock, flags);
3760
3761 if (new_table) {
3762 kmem_cache_free(amd_iommu_irq_cache, new_table->table);
3763 kfree(new_table);
3764 }
3765 return table;
3766}
3767
3768static int alloc_irq_index(u16 devid, int count, bool align)
3769{
3770 struct irq_remap_table *table;
3771 int index, c, alignment = 1;
3772 unsigned long flags;
3773 struct amd_iommu *iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
3774
3775 if (!iommu)
3776 return -ENODEV;
3777
3778 table = alloc_irq_table(devid);
3779 if (!table)
3780 return -ENODEV;
3781
3782 if (align)
3783 alignment = roundup_pow_of_two(count);
3784
3785 raw_spin_lock_irqsave(&table->lock, flags);
3786
3787 /* Scan table for free entries */
3788 for (index = ALIGN(table->min_index, alignment), c = 0;
3789 index < MAX_IRQS_PER_TABLE;) {
3790 if (!iommu->irte_ops->is_allocated(table, index)) {
3791 c += 1;
3792 } else {
3793 c = 0;
3794 index = ALIGN(index + 1, alignment);
3795 continue;
3796 }
3797
3798 if (c == count) {
3799 for (; c != 0; --c)
3800 iommu->irte_ops->set_allocated(table, index - c + 1);
3801
3802 index -= count - 1;
3803 goto out;
3804 }
3805
3806 index++;
3807 }
3808
3809 index = -ENOSPC;
3810
3811out:
3812 raw_spin_unlock_irqrestore(&table->lock, flags);
3813
3814 return index;
3815}

3817static int modify_irte_ga(u16 devid, int index, struct irte_ga *irte,
3818 struct amd_ir_data *data)
3819{
3820 struct irq_remap_table *table;
3821 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
3822 unsigned long flags;
3823 struct irte_ga *entry;
3824
3825 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
3826 if (iommu == NULL)
3827 return -EINVAL;
3828
3829 table = get_irq_table(devid);
3830 if (!table)
3831 return -ENOMEM;
3832
3833 raw_spin_lock_irqsave(&table->lock, flags);
3834
3835 entry = (struct irte_ga *)table->table;
3836 entry = &entry[index];
3837 entry->lo.fields_remap.valid = 0;
3838 entry->hi.val = irte->hi.val;
3839 entry->lo.val = irte->lo.val;
3840 entry->lo.fields_remap.valid = 1;
3841 if (data)
3842 data->ref = entry;
3843
3844 raw_spin_unlock_irqrestore(&table->lock, flags);
3845
3846 iommu_flush_irt(iommu, devid);
3847 iommu_completion_wait(iommu);
3848
3849 return 0;
3850}

4108static void irq_remapping_prepare_irte(struct amd_ir_data *data,
4109 struct irq_cfg *irq_cfg,
4110 struct irq_alloc_info *info,
4111 int devid, int index, int sub_handle)
4112{
4113 struct irq_2_irte *irte_info = &data->irq_2_irte;
4114 struct msi_msg *msg = &data->msi_entry;
4115 struct IO_APIC_route_entry *entry;
4116 struct amd_iommu *iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
4117
4118 if (!iommu)
4119 return;
4120
4121 data->irq_2_irte.devid = devid;
4122 data->irq_2_irte.index = index + sub_handle;
4123 iommu->irte_ops->prepare(data->entry, apic->irq_delivery_mode,
4124 apic->irq_dest_mode, irq_cfg->vector,
4125 irq_cfg->dest_apicid, devid);
4126
4127 switch (info->type) {
4128 case X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_IOAPIC:
4129 /* Setup IOAPIC entry */
4130 entry = info->ioapic_entry;
4131 info->ioapic_entry = NULL;
4132 memset(entry, 0, sizeof(*entry));
4133 entry->vector = index;
4134 entry->mask = 0;
4135 entry->trigger = info->ioapic_trigger;
4136 entry->polarity = info->ioapic_polarity;
4137 /* Mask level triggered irqs. */
4138 if (info->ioapic_trigger)
4139 entry->mask = 1;
4140 break;
4141
4142 case X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_HPET:
4143 case X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSI:
4144 case X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSIX:
4145 msg->address_hi = MSI_ADDR_BASE_HI;
4146 msg->address_lo = MSI_ADDR_BASE_LO;
4147 msg->data = irte_info->index;
4148 break;
4149
4150 default:
4151 BUG_ON(1);
4152 break;
4153 }
4154}

4176static int irq_remapping_alloc(struct irq_domain *domain, unsigned int virq,
4177 unsigned int nr_irqs, void *arg)
4178{
4179 struct irq_alloc_info *info = arg;
4180 struct irq_data *irq_data;
4181 struct amd_ir_data *data = NULL;
4182 struct irq_cfg *cfg;
4183 int i, ret, devid;
4184 int index;
4185
4186 if (!info)
4187 return -EINVAL;
4188 if (nr_irqs > 1 && info->type != X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSI &&
4189 info->type != X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSIX)
4190 return -EINVAL;
4191
4192 /*
4193 * With IRQ remapping enabled, don't need contiguous CPU vectors
4194 * to support multiple MSI interrupts.
4195 */
4196 if (info->type == X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSI)
4197 info->flags &= ~X86_IRQ_ALLOC_CONTIGUOUS_VECTORS;
4198
4199 devid = get_devid(info);
4200 if (devid < 0)
4201 return -EINVAL;
4202
4203 ret = irq_domain_alloc_irqs_parent(domain, virq, nr_irqs, arg);
4204 if (ret < 0)
4205 return ret;
4206
4207 if (info->type == X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_IOAPIC) {
4208 struct irq_remap_table *table;
4209 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
4210
4211 table = alloc_irq_table(devid);
4212 if (table) {
4213 if (!table->min_index) {
4214 /*
4215 * Keep the first 32 indexes free for IOAPIC
4216 * interrupts.
4217 */
4218 table->min_index = 32;
4219 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
4220 for (i = 0; i < 32; ++i)
4221 iommu->irte_ops->set_allocated(table, i);
4222 }
4223 WARN_ON(table->min_index != 32);
4224 index = info->ioapic_pin;
4225 } else {
4226 index = -ENOMEM;
4227 }
4228 } else {
4229 bool align = (info->type == X86_IRQ_ALLOC_TYPE_MSI);
4230
4231 index = alloc_irq_index(devid, nr_irqs, align);
4232 }
4233 if (index < 0) {
4234 pr_warn("Failed to allocate IRTE\n");
4235 ret = index;
4236 goto out_free_parent;
4237 }
4238
4239 for (i = 0; i < nr_irqs; i++) {
4240 irq_data = irq_domain_get_irq_data(domain, virq + i);
4241 cfg = irqd_cfg(irq_data);
4242 if (!irq_data || !cfg) {
4243 ret = -EINVAL;
4244 goto out_free_data;
4245 }
4246
4247 ret = -ENOMEM;
4248 data = kzalloc(sizeof(*data), GFP_KERNEL);
4249 if (!data)
4250 goto out_free_data;
4251
4252 if (!AMD_IOMMU_GUEST_IR_GA(amd_iommu_guest_ir))
4253 data->entry = kzalloc(sizeof(union irte), GFP_KERNEL);
4254 else
4255 data->entry = kzalloc(sizeof(struct irte_ga),
4256 GFP_KERNEL);
4257 if (!data->entry) {
4258 kfree(data);
4259 goto out_free_data;
4260 }
4261
4262 irq_data->hwirq = (devid << 16) + i;
4263 irq_data->chip_data = data;
4264 irq_data->chip = &amd_ir_chip;
4265 irq_remapping_prepare_irte(data, cfg, info, devid, index, i);
4266 irq_set_status_flags(virq + i, IRQ_MOVE_PCNTXT);
4267 }
4268
4269 return 0;
4270
4271out_free_data:
4272 for (i--; i >= 0; i--) {
4273 irq_data = irq_domain_get_irq_data(domain, virq + i);
4274 if (irq_data)
4275 kfree(irq_data->chip_data);
4276 }
4277 for (i = 0; i < nr_irqs; i++)
4278 free_irte(devid, index + i);
4279out_free_parent:
4280 irq_domain_free_irqs_common(domain, virq, nr_irqs);
4281 return ret;
4282}
4283
4284static void irq_remapping_free(struct irq_domain *domain, unsigned int virq,
4285 unsigned int nr_irqs)
4286{
4287 struct irq_2_irte *irte_info;
4288 struct irq_data *irq_data;
4289 struct amd_ir_data *data;
4290 int i;
4291
4292 for (i = 0; i < nr_irqs; i++) {
4293 irq_data = irq_domain_get_irq_data(domain, virq + i);
4294 if (irq_data && irq_data->chip_data) {
4295 data = irq_data->chip_data;
4296 irte_info = &data->irq_2_irte;
4297 free_irte(irte_info->devid, irte_info->index);
4298 kfree(data->entry);
4299 kfree(data);
4300 }
4301 }
4302 irq_domain_free_irqs_common(domain, virq, nr_irqs);
4303}

4346static int amd_ir_set_vcpu_affinity(struct irq_data *data, void *vcpu_info)
4347{
4348 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
4349 struct amd_iommu_pi_data *pi_data = vcpu_info;
4350 struct vcpu_data *vcpu_pi_info = pi_data->vcpu_data;
4351 struct amd_ir_data *ir_data = data->chip_data;
4352 struct irte_ga *irte = (struct irte_ga *) ir_data->entry;
4353 struct irq_2_irte *irte_info = &ir_data->irq_2_irte;
4354 struct iommu_dev_data *dev_data = search_dev_data(irte_info->devid);
4355
4356 /* Note:
4357 * This device has never been set up for guest mode.
4358 * we should not modify the IRTE
4359 */
4360 if (!dev_data || !dev_data->use_vapic)
4361 return 0;
4362
4363 pi_data->ir_data = ir_data;
4364
4365 /* Note:
4366 * SVM tries to set up for VAPIC mode, but we are in
4367 * legacy mode. So, we force legacy mode instead.
4368 */
4369 if (!AMD_IOMMU_GUEST_IR_VAPIC(amd_iommu_guest_ir)) {
4370 pr_debug("%s: Fall back to using intr legacy remap\n",
4371 __func__);
4372 pi_data->is_guest_mode = false;
4373 }
4374
4375 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[irte_info->devid];
4376 if (iommu == NULL)
4377 return -EINVAL;
4378
4379 pi_data->prev_ga_tag = ir_data->cached_ga_tag;
4380 if (pi_data->is_guest_mode) {
4381 /* Setting */
4382 irte->hi.fields.ga_root_ptr = (pi_data->base >> 12);
4383 irte->hi.fields.vector = vcpu_pi_info->vector;
4384 irte->lo.fields_vapic.ga_log_intr = 1;
4385 irte->lo.fields_vapic.guest_mode = 1;
4386 irte->lo.fields_vapic.ga_tag = pi_data->ga_tag;
4387
4388 ir_data->cached_ga_tag = pi_data->ga_tag;
4389 } else {
4390 /* Un-Setting */
4391 struct irq_cfg *cfg = irqd_cfg(data);
4392
4393 irte->hi.val = 0;
4394 irte->lo.val = 0;
4395 irte->hi.fields.vector = cfg->vector;
4396 irte->lo.fields_remap.guest_mode = 0;
4397 irte->lo.fields_remap.destination =
4398 APICID_TO_IRTE_DEST_LO(cfg->dest_apicid);
4399 irte->hi.fields.destination =
4400 APICID_TO_IRTE_DEST_HI(cfg->dest_apicid);
4401 irte->lo.fields_remap.int_type = apic->irq_delivery_mode;
4402 irte->lo.fields_remap.dm = apic->irq_dest_mode;
4403
4404 /*
4405 * This communicates the ga_tag back to the caller
4406 * so that it can do all the necessary clean up.
4407 */
4408 ir_data->cached_ga_tag = 0;
4409 }
4410
4411 return modify_irte_ga(irte_info->devid, irte_info->index, irte, ir_data);
4412}

4415static void amd_ir_update_irte(struct irq_data *irqd, struct amd_iommu *iommu,
4416 struct amd_ir_data *ir_data,
4417 struct irq_2_irte *irte_info,
4418 struct irq_cfg *cfg)
4419{
4420
4421 /*
4422 * Atomically updates the IRTE with the new destination, vector
4423 * and flushes the interrupt entry cache.
4424 */
4425 iommu->irte_ops->set_affinity(ir_data->entry, irte_info->devid,
4426 irte_info->index, cfg->vector,
4427 cfg->dest_apicid);
4428}

4430static int amd_ir_set_affinity(struct irq_data *data,
4431 const struct cpumask *mask, bool force)
4432{
4433 struct amd_ir_data *ir_data = data->chip_data;
4434 struct irq_2_irte *irte_info = &ir_data->irq_2_irte;
4435 struct irq_cfg *cfg = irqd_cfg(data);
4436 struct irq_data *parent = data->parent_data;
4437 struct amd_iommu *iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[irte_info->devid];
4438 int ret;
4439
4440 if (!iommu)
4441 return -ENODEV;
4442
4443 ret = parent->chip->irq_set_affinity(parent, mask, force);
4444 if (ret < 0 || ret == IRQ_SET_MASK_OK_DONE)
4445 return ret;
4446
4447 amd_ir_update_irte(data, iommu, ir_data, irte_info, cfg);
4448 /*
4449 * After this point, all the interrupts will start arriving
4450 * at the new destination. So, time to cleanup the previous
4451 * vector allocation.
4452 */
4453 send_cleanup_vector(cfg);
4454
4455 return IRQ_SET_MASK_OK_DONE;
4456}

4473int amd_iommu_create_irq_domain(struct amd_iommu *iommu)
4474{
4475 struct fwnode_handle *fn;
4476
4477 fn = irq_domain_alloc_named_id_fwnode("AMD-IR", iommu->index);
4478 if (!fn)
4479 return -ENOMEM;
4480 iommu->ir_domain = irq_domain_create_tree(fn, &amd_ir_domain_ops, iommu);
4481 irq_domain_free_fwnode(fn);
4482 if (!iommu->ir_domain)
4483 return -ENOMEM;
4484
4485 iommu->ir_domain->parent = arch_get_ir_parent_domain();
4486 iommu->msi_domain = arch_create_remap_msi_irq_domain(iommu->ir_domain,
4487 "AMD-IR-MSI",
4488 iommu->index);
4489 return 0;
4490}
4491
4492int amd_iommu_update_ga(int cpu, bool is_run, void *data)
4493{
4494 unsigned long flags;
4495 struct amd_iommu *iommu;
4496 struct irq_remap_table *table;
4497 struct amd_ir_data *ir_data = (struct amd_ir_data *)data;
4498 int devid = ir_data->irq_2_irte.devid;
4499 struct irte_ga *entry = (struct irte_ga *) ir_data->entry;
4500 struct irte_ga *ref = (struct irte_ga *) ir_data->ref;
4501
4502 if (!AMD_IOMMU_GUEST_IR_VAPIC(amd_iommu_guest_ir) ||
4503 !ref || !entry || !entry->lo.fields_vapic.guest_mode)
4504 return 0;
4505
4506 iommu = amd_iommu_rlookup_table[devid];
4507 if (!iommu)
4508 return -ENODEV;
4509
4510 table = get_irq_table(devid);
4511 if (!table)
4512 return -ENODEV;
4513
4514 raw_spin_lock_irqsave(&table->lock, flags);
4515
4516 if (ref->lo.fields_vapic.guest_mode) {
4517 if (cpu >= 0) {
4518 ref->lo.fields_vapic.destination =
4519 APICID_TO_IRTE_DEST_LO(cpu);
4520 ref->hi.fields.destination =
4521 APICID_TO_IRTE_DEST_HI(cpu);
4522 }
4523 ref->lo.fields_vapic.is_run = is_run;
4524 barrier();
4525 }
4526
4527 raw_spin_unlock_irqrestore(&table->lock, flags);
4528
4529 iommu_flush_irt(iommu, devid);
4530 iommu_completion_wait(iommu);
4531 return 0;
4532}
